         <t:abstract><t:p>The Gadl of St Libānos (Maṭāʿ) exists in three different recensions, the most frequent being <t:ref target="#recension2">the second one</t:ref>. 
            The text is attributed to ʾElyās, the Bishop of Aksum (cp. <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmgm012">Gāntā ʾAfašum, Mǝʾǝsār Gwǝḥilā Qǝddus Mikāʾel, MGM-012</t:ref>, 
            <t:locus target="#17ra">17ra</t:locus>).</t:p></t:abstract>
         <t:textClass>
